<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,818,567,594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">
Problems with the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[540,818,567,593]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,818,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Psilorhynchus kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,567,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">
Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[301,349,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
. (2018) described 
<taxonomicName box="[550,660,602,625]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kunawa">
<emphasis box="[550,660,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kunawa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount box="[769,914,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="generic">16 specimens</specimenCount>
collected from a single location (Kuwana River, Pathar Village, Devario District, 
<collectingRegion box="[512,663,637,660]" country="India" name="Uttar Pradesh" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Uttar Pradesh</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[676,735,637,660]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">India</collectingCountry>
). Based on the characters listed in the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1436,637,660]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[312,361,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
., 2018: 218–222) and based on the gestalt of the 
<typeStatus box="[908,1001,672,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">holotype</typeStatus>
(Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[1172,1220,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
., 2018; Fig. 5) it is apparent that this species is very similar in external appearance to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[898,1005,706,729]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[898,1005,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare the 
<typeStatus box="[1169,1262,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shown in figure 5 of Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[612,658,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
., 2018 with any specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[972,1075,741,764]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[972,1075,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated in Conway 
<emphasis box="[1316,1363,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
., 2013 [figures 3–7]). In the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Arunachalam et al. (2018: 219)" authorityName="Arunachalam et al." authorityPageNumber="219" authorityYear="2018" box="[518,978,776,799]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[518,634,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana,</emphasis>
Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[792,839,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
. (2018: 219)
</taxonomicName>
list eight characters (
<tableCitation box="[1208,1289,776,799]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[125,204,558,579]" captionText="TABLE 2. Reassessment of characters reported todistinguish Psilorhynchus kuwana from P. sucatioin Arunachalam et al.(2018) in comparison to information available fromConway et. (2013) or derived subsequent to that study but based on the same material (***). Values in bold indicate those which can not be repeated based either on information available in Arunachalam et al.(2018)or examination ofmaterial ofP.sucatio." pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Table 2</tableCitation>
) that serve to differentiate the allegedly new species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[620,723,810,833]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[620,723,810,833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Again, critical reappraisal of these characters (
<tableCitation box="[1227,1307,810,833]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[125,204,558,579]" captionText="TABLE 2. Reassessment of characters reported todistinguish Psilorhynchus kuwana from P. sucatioin Arunachalam et al.(2018) in comparison to information available fromConway et. (2013) or derived subsequent to that study but based on the same material (***). Values in bold indicate those which can not be repeated based either on information available in Arunachalam et al.(2018)or examination ofmaterial ofP.sucatio." pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Table 2</tableCitation>
) reveals the same issues as raised above for 
<taxonomicName box="[525,696,845,868]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platydorsalis">
<emphasis box="[525,696,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. platydorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1033,845,868]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[918,1033,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is especially plagued by “ephemeral” characters, which are no longer valid when the actual variation present within 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1170,1276,880,903]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[1170,1276,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered. Worryingly, Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[435,482,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
. (2018) report the upper jaw to be of widely different lengths in 
<taxonomicName box="[1173,1282,914,937]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[1173,1282,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“11.3–16.5”) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[198,304,949,972]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[198,304,949,972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“26.3–30.1%HL”) and thus of some use in distinguishing between the two species. Given that (1) the length of the upper jaw is relatively uniform across 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M'Clelland" authorityYear="1839" box="[711,863,984,1007]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,863,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Psilorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., see Figure 
<quantity box="[1051,1093,984,1007]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="ConWay, K. W." box="[1100,1256,984,1007]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="50 – 154" part="163" refId="ref3117" refString="ConWay, K. W. (2011) Osteology of the South Asian genus Psilorhynchus M'Clelland, 1839 (Teleostei: Ostariophysi: Psilorhynchidae) With inVestigation of its phylogenetic relationships Within the Order Cypriniformes. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 163, 50 - 154." title="Osteology of the South Asian genus Psilorhynchus M’Clelland, 1839 (Teleostei: Ostariophysi: Psilorhynchidae) With inVestigation of its phylogenetic relationships Within the Order Cypriniformes" type="journal article" year="2011">Conway, 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and (2) that the upper jaw is not visible externally and cannot be measured accurately using point to point calipers (the method reported by Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[350,405,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
., 2018) the differences reported in this character between 
<taxonomicName box="[1098,1215,1053,1076]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[1098,1215,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1283,1394,1053,1076]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[1283,1394,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[301,347,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
. (2018) cannot be explained or credited.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,567,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">
Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[351,400,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">et al</emphasis>
. (2018) have failed to provide convincing character evidence that 
<taxonomicName box="[1128,1239,1122,1145]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[1128,1239,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[209,313,1157,1180]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[209,313,1157,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore 
<taxonomicName box="[467,576,1157,1180]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuwana">
<emphasis box="[467,576,1157,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. kuwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[829,933,1157,1180]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Psilorhynchidae" genus="Psilorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sucatio">
<emphasis box="[829,933,1157,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">P. sucatio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
